Field Detail

BROWSER

static final Dimension BROWSER
The names of browsers used by visitors to your website. For example, "Internet Explorer" or "Firefox." The version of the browser is not returned in this field.

BROWSER_VERSION

static final Dimension BROWSER_VERSION
The browser versions used by visitors to your site. For example, 2.0.0.14

CITY

static final Dimension CITY
The cities of site visitors, derived from IP addresses. The city field falls in a hierarchy of geographical groupings used in Analytics, which proceeds in the following order: continent, sub-continent, country, region, sub-region, and city.

CONNECTION_SPEED

static final Dimension CONNECTION_SPEED
The qualitative network connection speeds of site visitors. For example, T1, DSL, Cable, Dialup.

CONTINENT

static final Dimension CONTINENT
The continents of site visitors, derived from IP addresses.

COUNT_OF_VISITS

static final Dimension COUNT_OF_VISITS
Number of visits to your site. This is calculated by determining the number of visitor sessions. For example, if a visitor comes to your site, exits their browser, and 5 minutes later visits your site again via the same browser, that is calculated as 2 visits.

COUNTRY

static final Dimension COUNTRY
The countries of site visitors, derived from IP addresses.

DATE

static final Dimension DATE
The date of the visit. An integer in the form YYYYMMDD.

DAY

static final Dimension DAY
The day of the month from 01 to 31.

DAYS_SINCE_LAST_VISIT

static final Dimension DAYS_SINCE_LAST_VISIT
The number of days elapsed since visitors last visited the site. Used to calculate visitor loyalty. For example, if you view this field in a report on 5/20, and some visitors last visited your site on 5/15, the value for this would be 5, reported as "5 days ago."

FLASH_VERSION

static final Dimension FLASH_VERSION
The versions of Flash supported by visitors' browsers, including minor versions.

HOSTNAME

static final Dimension HOSTNAME
The hostnames visitors used to reach your site. In other words, if some visitors use www.googlestore.com to reach your site, this string appears as one of the hostnames used to reach your site. However, if other visitors also come to your site via googlestore.com or via an IP redirect from a search engine result (66.102.9.104), those values will also be present in this field.

HOUR

static final Dimension HOUR
A two digit hour of the day ranging from 00-23. (Google Analytics does not track visitor time more precisely than hours.) Note: Combining this dimension with AD_CONTENT is not currently supported.

JAVA_ENABLED

static final Dimension JAVA_ENABLED
Whether the visitor has Java support enabled on their browser. The possible values are Yes or No.

LANGUAGE

static final Dimension LANGUAGE
This field uses the language as provided by the HTTP Request for the browser to determine the primary languages used by visitors. Values are given as an ISO-639 code (e.g. en-gb for British English).

LATITUDE

static final Dimension LATITUDE
The approximate latitude of the visitor's city. Locations north of the equator are represented by positive values and locations south of the equator by negative values.

LONGITUDE

static final Dimension LONGITUDE
The approximate longitude of the visitor's city. Locations east of the meridian are represented by positive values and locations west of the meridian by negative values.

MONTH

static final Dimension MONTH
The month of the visit. A two digit integer from 01 to 12.

NETWORK_DOMAIN

static final Dimension NETWORK_DOMAIN
The domain name of the ISPs used by visitors to your website.

NETWORK_LOCATION

static final Dimension NETWORK_LOCATION
The name of service providers used to reach your site. For example, if most visitors to your site come via the major service providers for cable internet, you will see the names of those cable service providers in this element.

PAGE_DEPTH

static final Dimension PAGE_DEPTH
The number of pages visited by visitors during a session (visit). The value is a histogram that counts pageviews across a range of possible values. In this calculation, all visits will have at least one pageview, and some percentage of visits will have more.

OPERATING_SYSTEM

static final Dimension OPERATING_SYSTEM
The operating system used by your visitors. For example, Windows, Linux, Macintosh, iPhone, iPod.

OPERATING_SYSTEM_VERSION

static final Dimension OPERATING_SYSTEM_VERSION
The version of the operating system used by your visitors, such as XP for Windows or PPC for Macintosh.

REGION

static final Dimension REGION
The region of site visitors, derived from IP addresses. In the U.S., a region is a state, such as New York.

SCREEN_COLORS

static final Dimension SCREEN_COLORS
The color depth of visitors' monitors, as retrieved from the DOM of the visitor's browser. Values include 4-bit, 8-bit, 24-bit, or undefined-bit.

SCREEN_RESOLUTION

static final Dimension SCREEN_RESOLUTION
The screen resolution of visitors' monitors, as retrieved from the DOM of the visitor's browser. For example: 1024x738.

SUB_CONTINENT

static final Dimension SUB_CONTINENT
The sub-continent of site visitors, derived from IP addresses. For example, Polynesia or Northern Europe.

USER_DEFINED_VALUE

static final Dimension USER_DEFINED_VALUE
The value provided when you define custom visitor segments for your site. For more information, see Creating Custom Visitor Segments.

VISITOR_TYPE

static final VisitorTypeDimension VISITOR_TYPE
A boolean indicating if visitors are new or returning. Possible values: New Visitor, Returning Visitor.

WEEK

static final Dimension WEEK
The week of the visit. A two-digit number from 01 to 52.

YEAR

static final Dimension YEAR
The year of the visit. A four-digit year from 2005 to the current year.

AD_CONTENT

static final Dimension AD_CONTENT
The first line of the text for your online Ad campaign. If you are using mad libs for your AdWords content, this field displays the keywords you provided for the mad libs keyword match. Note: Combining this dimension with HOUR is not currently supported.

AD_GROUP

static final Dimension AD_GROUP
The ad groups that you have identified for your campaign keywords. For example, you might have an ad group toys which you associate with the keywords fuzzy bear.

AD_SLOT

static final Dimension AD_SLOT
The position of the advertisement as it appears on the host page. For example, the online advertising position might be side or top.

AD_SLOT_POSITION

static final Dimension AD_SLOT_POSITION
The order of the online advertisement as it appears along with other ads in the position on the page. For example, the ad might appear on the right side of the page and be the 3rd ad from the top.

CAMPAIGN

static final Dimension CAMPAIGN
The name(s) of the online ad campaign that you use for your website.

KEYWORD

static final Dimension KEYWORD
The keywords used by visitors to reach your site, via both paid ads and through search engine results.

MEDIUM

static final Dimension MEDIUM
The type of referral to your website. For example, when referring sources to your website are search engines, there are a number of possible mediums that can be used from a search engine referral: from a search result (organic) and from an online ad on the search results page (CPC, ppc, cpa, CPM, cpv, cpp).

REFERRAL_PATH

static final Dimension REFERRAL_PATH
The path of the referring URL. If someone places a link to your site on their website, this element contains the path of the page that contains the referring link.

SOURCE

static final Dimension SOURCE
The domain (e.g. google.com) of the source referring the visitor to your website. The value for this dimension sometimes contains a port address as well.

EXIT_PAGE_PATH

static final Dimension EXIT_PAGE_PATH
The last page of the session (or "exit" page) for your visitors.

LANDING_PAGE_PATH

static final Dimension LANDING_PAGE_PATH
The path component of the URL of the entrance or "landing" page for your visitors.

PAGE_PATH

static final Dimension PAGE_PATH
The page on your website by path and/or query parameters.

PAGE_TITLE

static final Dimension PAGE_TITLE
The title for the page, as specified in the <title></title> element of the HTML document.

AFFILIATION

static final Dimension AFFILIATION
Typically used to designate a supplying company or brick and mortar location; product affiliation.

DAYS_TO_TRANSACTION

static final Dimension DAYS_TO_TRANSACTION
The number of days between users' purchases and the related campaigns that lead to the purchases.

PRODUCT_CATEGORY

static final Dimension PRODUCT_CATEGORY
Any product variations (size, color) for purchased items as supplied by your ecommerce application.

PRODUCT_NAME

static final Dimension PRODUCT_NAME
The product name for purchased items as supplied by your ecommerce tracking method.

PRODUCT_SKU

static final Dimension PRODUCT_SKU
The product codes for purchased items as you have defined them in your ecommerce tracking application.

TRANSACTION_ID

static final Dimension TRANSACTION_ID
The transaction ID for the shopping cart purchase as supplied by your ecommerce tracking method.

SEARCH_CATEGORY

static final Dimension SEARCH_CATEGORY
If you have categories enabled for internal site search, this field identifies the categories used for the internal search. For example, you might have product categories for internal search, such as electronics, furniture, or clothing.

SEARCH_DESTINATION_PAGE

static final Dimension SEARCH_DESTINATION_PAGE
The page that the user visited after performing an internal site search.

SEARCH_KEYWORD

static final Dimension SEARCH_KEYWORD
Search terms used by site visitors on your internal site search.

SEARCH_KEYWORD_REFINEMENT

static final Dimension SEARCH_KEYWORD_REFINEMENT
Subsequent keyword search terms or strings entered by users after a given initial string search.

SEARCH_START_PAGE

static final Dimension SEARCH_START_PAGE
The page where the user initiated an internal site search.

SEARCH_USED

static final Dimension SEARCH_USED
A boolean which separates visitor activity depending upon whether internal search activity occured or did not occur. Values are Visits With Site Search and Visits Without Site Search.
